<item>
            <title>[SPR-1175] Reading old value from BeanWrapperImpl can cause compatibility problems</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1175</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;In the new Version 1.2.3 there has been a change in BeanWrapperImpl (as indicated in the changelog) that BeanWrapperImpl will pass along the old value to setAsText().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently I have the situation that I require the setter being invoked, before accessing the value. So I throw an exception if the property is not set on use. Since setting the value now invokes the getter first, the code breaks (it&apos;s a central thing and not easily changed).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some sort of &quot;compatibility mode&quot; with the old behaviour would be nice.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
