                            <comment id="14123" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 27 Jul 2005 18:05:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, if the getter throws an exception, that exception should simply get logged at debug level (BeanWrapperImpl.java: 834-841). Which specific failure did you encounter nevertheless?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14126" author="asenft" created="Wed, 27 Jul 2005 22:07:33 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;You are right. I have been misled by an own logging at error level which has been caused by the failing getter invocation. Unfortunately there had been another problem (which has nothing to do with spring) which made me think that the getter invocation made the application fail.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sorry for the inconvenience. This issue can be closed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Andreas&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14127" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 27 Jul 2005 22:24:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No problem &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14167" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sun, 31 Jul 2005 21:50:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As of Spring 1.2.4, the BeanWrapper will only extract the old value for a property if explicitly told to do so via the newly introduced &quot;setExtractOldValueForEditor&quot; method. This flag will by default only be set for the DataBinder (where it is actually relevant), but not for a BeanFactory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
